name: Mission Creek Cafe
directions: Head straight back. behind a divider.

name: Rainbow Grocery Co-op
directions: behind customer server, near the parking garage
comment: need a key --- on cust service desk. sometimes they're both taken, wait by the comment board

name: Coffee To The People
directions: towards the rear of the coffee shop.

name: Cafe Roma
directions: down a steep flight of stairs!
comment: kinda sketch, but hey, it's a place to pee in north beach...

name: Philz Coffee
directions: to the right of the counter, in back

name: Bang San Thai Restuarant
comment: two single stall gendered. different owners from mekong (closed in 2008) but still a nice place

name: Pottery Barn
comment: You may have to walk around and pretend that you're looking at stuff to use the restrooms. There are 2 stalls (gendered) and they both lock. It's in a corner, so no one will really see which stall anyone goes into.

name: Sparky's Diner
directions: in the back, down some steps
comment: two single stalls. gender binary not rigidly enforced, people of a variety of genders openly use either.

name: Muddy Water's Coffee
directions: in the back, you need to be buzzed in

name: GLBT Historical Society
directions: 3rd Floor, has elevator. Open Tues-Sat, 1-5 pm.
comment: Also worth a visit for their collection of GLBT historical material!

name: El Rio
directions: Back right of main bar room.
comment: Restrooms are labeled based on hardware available: urinals in one, toilets in the other. Not labeled by gender.

name: LGBT Community Center
directions: Gender-free restroom on the main floor near the elevators, and also in the Three Dollar Bill Cafe.

name: maggie mudd ice cream
comment: amazing vegan ice cream! genderfree, locking, accessible, changing station.
